Heat oil on medium heat in a large (4 L/16 cup) pot. Add next 4 ingredients. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes, or until onions are tender. Add potatoes and stock. Bring to a boil, cover and lower heat. Simmer 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Add Carnation(R) Milk and cook for an additional 5 minutes. Puree half the soup. Return to pot and combine well. Stir in dill. Add salt to taste.